article.headline: Campbell 95, Lipscomb 91
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Maurice Latham scored 29 points on 11-of-13 shooting as Campbell outlasted Lipscomb 95-91 Wednesday. Campbell (4-7, 3-1 Atlantic Sun) led by as much as 17 points in the second half and survived a late rally by Lipscomb (6-6, 2-2), which trailed only 91-89 with 26 seconds left on a layup by Brian Fisk. Latham then scored on a fast break and Reggie Bishop added two free throws to make it 95-89. Lipscomb's Michael Lusk made a layup with 2 seconds left. Jake Wohlfeil had 14 points for Campbell, followed by Eric Smith with 11 and Ledell Eackles and Bishop with 10 each. Eddie Ard led the Bisons with 24 points, Fisk had 22, James Poindexter 17 and Shaun Durant 10. The Camels shot 55.9 percent for the game and Lipscomb 49.3 percent. Campbell led 48-34 at the half.
